As for these three Particles, Où where, wherein, whether;
Y, in it, of it, there; En, of it, some, any; they are often
used like Relative Pronouns; as,

                                       Ie me faut de l'argent, I must have (or I want) Money; 
                                          〈◊〉

so in other Tenses and Persons.

* Note that in the third Person Singular, there is a (
