2. A Comma (,) marks the little pauses one makes in a
Discourse, both to grace it, and to make it clear to the Reader;
as,

Vraiment je ne saurois;
voyez si vous voulez joüer du
pair?

Que je voye; Tenez le miroir;
Dieux! j'ay un visage a
saire peur aujourd' huy.

Pick (or fleece) them Pullets;
draw them, tuck them up well,
and lard them neatly.

